 Suspected adherents of the proscribed Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) have allegedly seized Ugbolu town in Oshimili North local government area of Delta State. The uprising, according to residents of the area started at 9 p.m. on Thursday. They were said to be shooting guns and chanting hymns of war and insisting that there would be no election. The fear of the unknown has made residents of the town to be panicking.
